          "params": [],
          "returnType": null,
          "description": "Drive amount: controls the intensity of the tanh soft-clip curve. Range 0..1, default 0.4. Higher values produce heavier, more saturated distortion; lower values produce a milder soft-clip. Note that even at drive=0 the curve is not perfectly linear — the formula tanh(x) / tanh(1) has a gain of 1/tanh(1) ≈ 1.31 at the origin."
        },
        {
          "name": "oversample",
          "signature": "oversample?: OverSampleType",
          "signatureTokens": [
